The Middleton Police Department is a full-service police department commanded by Chief Steven Thompson.  The Field Services division is commanded by Captain Jeremy Geiszler and consists of 21 patrol officers, 4 Sergeants & 3 Lieutenants, as well as the Investigative Services Bureau, consisting of one Lieutenant, 4 Investigators, 3 School Resource Officers and 1 Community Awareness Officer. 

The Administrative Services division is commanded by Captain Tyler Loether and consists of an Office Manager, 2 Records Clerks, a Court Officer/Evidence Manager, a Dispatch Center Supervisor, and 8 full-time Dispatchers.

